“That depends on the length of the speech,” answered the President. “If it is a ten-minute speech it takes me all of two weeks to prepare it; if...Read moreThat reminded me of this quote, which I’ve known for many years (I believe I read it on “Reader’s Digest” over 30 years ago, but I’m not sure)
“How long does it take you to prepare one of your speeches?” asked a friend of President Wilson not long ago.
“That depends on the length of the speech,” answered the President. “If it is a ten-minute speech it takes me all of two weeks to prepare it; if it is a half-hour speech it takes me a week; if I can talk as long as I want to it requires no preparation at all. I am ready now.”
(lifted from this reference: https://quoteinvestigator.com/2014/03/01/short-speech/ )
